I was trying to add some new pages and the multi- media plugin just spins.  It won't load.  I tried using it with both Chrome and Safari.  Same results.  It is just blank and never loads the dialog..  

I also tried to copy and existing entry to the new page.  It again just spins when I try to assign the movie content. Even when I went to a new instance I was showing the same issue.

{panel}
*Workaround 1*

Drag and drop the video file directly into the editor. Confluence will automatically attach the file and insert the multimedia macro.

*Workaround 2*

If you need to edit the macro parameters you can use wikimarkup.

1. In the editor Go to *Insert* > *Markup* and enter the wikimarkup based on the examples below. 
2. The multimedia macro placeholder will appear in the preview when the wikimarkup has been entered correctly.  
3. Click *Insert* to insert it into your page. 

To embed a multimedia file attached to the current page enter:
{code}{multimedia:name=filename.mov} {code}
To embed a multimedia file attached to a page in another space and make it autoplay enter:
{code}{multimedia:space=SPACEKEY|page=Page Title|name=filename.mov|autostart=true}{code}

Note: You still wont be able to edit the macro parameters in the macro browser, and if you need to make a change, you will need to insert the wikimarkup again.  More info on the parameters can be found on [this page|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Multimedia+Macro] {panel}

